ASMP has recieved a raw deal from the press.  As I understand it, 
Jack Dongarra (father of LinPack, Eispack, etc) found that ASMP is in
general faster for most problems than SMP, and you dont have to rewrite
your codes as much as for SMP.  This is from a paper of his that I read
last year comparing LINDA, PVM and a few other SMP and ASMP systems.

PVM allows for hetrogenous ASMP and a former professor and occasional 
collaborator at Michigan State University tells me that his code is now
nearly an order of magnitude faster after being adapted to ASMP, as compared
to the massively parallel (SMP) system it used to run on....  OS/2 has
PVM, and I am sure it wouldnt be to hard to put on NT.  I plan
to port my code over to it relatively soon.  (along with the other hundred
things on my IMPORTANT-to-do list :( )

SMP is great for the few apps designed for it.  

